title: Clemson Jumps to #3 in Newest AP Poll
text:
Clemson Jumps to #3 in Newest AP Poll Tools 
Story Created: Oct 25, 2015 at 3:11 PM   25, 2015 at 3:11 PM EDT CLEMSON, S.C. -- Clemson (7-0, 4-0 ACC) jumped three spots to #3 in the Associated Press top 25 poll. The ranking comes after a 58-0 thrashing of Miami in Miami Gardens. Clemson also received six first-place votes in the AP poll, the most since 1984. The Tigers' #3 ranking is the highest Clemson has been ranked in the AP poll since Oct. 13, 2013. Photo courtesy: @Clemsonfb
